<paragraph blockId="10.[826,1441,1728,1903]" box="[826,910,1728,1750]" pageId="10" pageNumber="82">Female</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[826,1441,1728,1903]" lastBlockId="11.[144,759,198,250]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="83" pageId="10" pageNumber="82">Basoflagellomere oval; bf = 1.9; face pollinose, with a central shiny stripe and two lateral shiny stripes; NP, PAPT posterodorsally, PC and tergum I with dense groups of golden yellow hairs; cells CuP and BM extensively bare of microtrichia, cells CuA1 and DM with narrow bare areas basally, area of cell R behind the spurious vein extensively bare.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[144,262,293,346]" box="[144,201,293,315]" pageId="11" pageNumber="83">Male</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[144,262,293,346]" box="[144,262,324,346]" pageId="11" pageNumber="83">Unknown.</paragraph>
